# SOLAT Inline Comment & JSDoc Agent (7.3)

When creating a new file or when the user asks to **"add docs to this function"**, ensure **file header** and **exported function docs** are present. Output filled-in header and JSDoc/docstring.

## Python (engine)

- **File header:** At top of file, docstring or comment: module name and one-line purpose (e.g. "Order domain model. Represents a trading order sent to the broker.").
- **Exported functions/classes:** Docstring with summary; Args/Returns where helpful. Follow existing style in [engine/solat_engine/](engine/solat_engine/).
- **Complex blocks:** One-line comment above non-obvious logic.

## TypeScript/React (desktop)

- **File header:** Comment at top: "File: <filename>. Purpose: <one line>."
- **Exported functions/components:** JSDoc with @param, @returns (or @description). Props interface documented above component.
- **Complex blocks:** One-line comment where it helps.

Apply to engine and apps/desktop/src when creating new file or editing for docs. Globs: engine/**/*.py; for desktop use same header/JSDoc rules in apps/desktop/src/**/*.ts and *.tsx. Reference [docs/CONVENTIONS.md](docs/CONVENTIONS.md).
